Linux already provides logrotate.
For production Linux servers (RHEL / Ubuntu / Debian / Oracle Linux), using built-in logrotate is usually preferred over a custom shell script.

Example configuration:

Create file:

sudo vi /etc/logrotate.d/myapp

Add:

/var/log/myapp.log {
    daily
    rotate 7
    compress
    missingok
    notifempty
    create 0644 root root
}

Test configuration:
logrotate -d /etc/logrotate.conf

Force rotation:
logrotate -f /etc/logrotate.conf
